{"title_page": "Intentions (Justin Bieber song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 single by Justin Bieber featuring Quavo}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name         = Intentions\n| type         = single\n| artist       = [[Justin Bieber]] featuring [[Quavo]]\n| album        = [[Changes (Justin Bieber album)|Changes]]\n| cover        = Justin Bieber - Intentions.png\n| alt          =\n| released     = {{start date|2020|2|7|mf=yes}}\n| format       = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded     =  \n| studio       =\n| genre        = \n| length       = 3:32\n| label        = [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]]\n| writer       = {{hlist|[[Justin Bieber]]|[[Quavo|Quavious Marshall]]|[[Poo Bear|Jason Boyd]]|[[The Audibles|Dominic Jordan]]|[[The Audibles|Jimmy Giannos]]}}\n| producer     = {{hlist|[[Poo Bear]]|[[The Audibles]]}}\n| chronology   = [[Justin Bieber]]\n| prev_title   = [[Yummy (Justin Bieber song)|Yummy]]\n| prev_year    = 2020\n| next_title   = [[Forever (Justin Bieber song)|Forever]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n| misc         = {{Extra chronology\n| artist = [[Quavo]]\n| type = singles\n| prev_title   = [[Had Enough (Don Toliver song)|Had Enough]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| title        = Intentions\n| year         = 2020\n| next_title   = Big Drip (Remix)\n| next_year    = 2020\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|9p2wMpVVtXg|\"Intentions\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Intentions'''\" is a song by Canadian singer [[Justin Bieber]] featuring American rapper [[Quavo]] from the hip-hop trio [[Migos]]. It was released on February 7, 2020, as the second single from Bieber's fifth studio album ''[[Changes (Justin Bieber album)|Changes]]'', with a music video.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2020-02-05-justin-bieber-announces-new-single-with-quavo-ahead-of-changes-release/|title=Justin Bieber Announces New Single With Quavo Ahead Of 'Changes' Release|website=[[iHeartRadio]]|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/justin-biebers-changes-album-will-feature-new-quavo-collaboration-intention|title=Justin Bieber\u2019s Changes album will feature new Quavo collaboration \"Intentions\"|website=[[The Line of Best Fit]]|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> This is their third collaboration since they both featured alongside American rapper [[Chance the Rapper]] on both [[DJ Khaled]]'s \"[[I'm the One (DJ Khaled song)|I'm the One]]\", with an extra feature from American rapper [[Lil Wayne]] in 2017 and \"[[No Brainer (song)|No Brainer]]\" in 2018. Bieber debuted the song with Quavo and \"[[Yummy (Justin Bieber song)|Yummy]]\" during ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' on February 8, 2020. He and Quavo also performed \"Intentions\" on February 14, 2020, the day the album released, during ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'' . He and Quavo also performed \"Intentions\" on March 4, 2020 on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]''. On March 19, 2020, Bieber released an acoustic version of the song, without Quavo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/justin-bieber-intentions-acoustic-969659/|title=Justin Bieber Drops Acoustic Version of 'Intentions'|last=Shaffer|first=Claire|last2=Shaffer|first2=Claire|date=2020-03-19|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n\"Intentions\" debuted at number 11 on the US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot 100]] chart dated February 22, 2020, eventually peaking at number eight. It also debuted at number one on the [[Hot R&B Songs]] chart, marking Bieber's third number 1, following \"[[Yummy (Justin Bieber song)|Yummy]]\", which \"Intentions\" dethroned.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8551188/roddy-ricch-the-box-number-one-sixth-week|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Rules Hot 100 For Sixth Week, Dua Lipa Matches Career Best With 'Don't Start Now'|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=February 18, 2020|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video premiered on Bieber's [[YouTube]] channel the same day of the song. It shows both artists helping people without an education and meeting them. Bieber published a lyric video to his channel on February 10, 2020. He then posted a short version of the music video, only the parts with the song playing, on February 12, 2020. Part of the filming took place at [[California State University, Northridge]]'s [[Oviatt Library]].\n\n== Credits and personnel ==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/131190301|title=''Changes'' / Justin Bieber|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>\n\n* [[Justin Bieber]] \u2013 lead vocals, songwriter\n* [[Quavo]] \u2013 featured vocals, songwriter\n* [[Poo Bear]] \u2013 producer, songwriter, backing vocals\n* [[The Audibles]] \u2013 producer, songwriter\n* Josh Gudwin \u2013 vocal producer, recording engineer, studio personnel\n* Chris \"TEK\" O'Ryan \u2013 recording engineer, studio personnel\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n| 2\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|11|artist=Justin Bieber feat. Quavo|song=Intentions|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|17|artist=Justin Bieber feat. Quavo|song=Intentions|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 7, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|1|artist=Justin Bieber feat. Quavo|song=Intentions|rowheader=tr